Locality: Alligator River NWR--Miltail Road Boat Launch
Media notes: This seems to me to be one of the best recordings I have made. The foreground catbird is very clear and gives 2 different kinds of calls--the standard meow calls and the double click calls that I have never before been able to get on a recording. Also, for comparison, the yellow-bellied sapsucker gives two or three of its very similar meows, and when viewed in the spectogram so close together the difference is accentuated.

Locality: Burnt Corn Creek at Jane's Mill Road
Observation Details:
Counted one by one. There were 8 different birds feeding on the road (east of the bridge) as I first arrived Just Before Sunrise.  When I walked the east side my count was 17.
 Six more along west side of bridge.

Continuing pair at (48.6540559, -122.2043717) flying around the downed power line right behind the 20 mph yellow corner street sign. One was calling and one was singing. The calling one was pretty friendly but the singing one was skittish. Photos and audio recorded.

Background Species: Vireo olivaceus -- Red-eyed Vireo; Corvus brachyrhynchos -- American Crow; Cardinalis cardinalis -- Northern Cardinal
